# WHAT IT IS
#   `lemmy_server` is a **single-binary federated link-aggregator
#   backend** that exposes:
#
#     • A REST + WebSocket API on the configured HTTP port that
#       the canonical Lemmy-UI frontend (lemmynet/lemmy-ui) +
#       third-party clients (mlmym, photon, jerboa-android,
#       voyager, eternity-for-lemmy, sublinks/sublinks-app,
#       summit-for-lemmy, lemmios, lurker) connect to
#
#     • An ActivityPub Server-to-Server federation surface
#       (Inbox / Outbox / followers / following endpoints; the
#       full set of typed `Create<Post>`, `Update<Post>`,
#       `Delete<Post>`, `Like<Post>`, `Dislike<Post>`,
#       `Create<Note>` (comment), `Update<Note>`, `Delete<Note>`,
#       `Like<Note>`, `Dislike<Note>`, `Follow<Community>`,
#       `Accept<Follow>`, `Reject<Follow>`, `Undo<Follow>`,
#       `Undo<Like>`, `Undo<Dislike>`, `Announce<Activity>`
#       (the canonical Lemmy `Group`-as-Community
#       boost mechanism), `Block<Person>`, `Move<Account>`
#       (Mastodon-style account migration), `Add<Moderator>`,
#       `Remove<Moderator>`, `Lock<Post>`, `Update<Page>`,
#       `Question<Vote>`, `Delete<Person>` activity types,
#       backed by HTTP Signature signing/verification against
#       the federated peer instance's `as:publicKey`,
#       webfinger resolution at `/.well-known/webfinger`, and
#       a NodeInfo 2.x advertisement at `/.well-known/nodeinfo`
#       /  `/nodeinfo/2.1.json` matching the ActivityPub-
#       Networks NodeInfo schema)
#
#     • Outbound activity sending workers that batch federated
#       deliveries to peer instances with per-instance backoff,
#       failure detection, and the canonical
#       `--federate-process-index` / `--federate-process-count`
#       horizontal-scaling sharding scheme (split the outbound
#       federation workload across N workers — each one only
#       handles activities whose `community_id % N == i-1`)
#
#     • Scheduled background tasks (federation-instance health
#       sweeps, mod-log retention, vote-aging adjustments,
#       database vacuum, optional outbound prometheus metrics
#       export, plugin-event dispatch)
#
#     • A diesel-driven PostgreSQL schema with full ACID
#       transaction semantics, supporting partitioned-by-community
#       activity queues, federated mention indices, comment-tree
#       materialization for fast post-page rendering, full-text
#       search via PostgreSQL `tsvector` columns, image proxy
#       caching, and a custom plugin sandbox loaded via the
#       `lemmy_plugins` framework
#
#   Bootstrap workflow:
#     1. `lemmy_server migration run --all`       run schema
#                                                  migrations
#     2. `lemmy_server --disable-activity-sending` boot up the
#                                                  HTTP API only
#                                                  (single-server
#                                                  trial mode)
#     3. `lemmy_server --federate-process-index N --federate-process-count M`
#                                                  scale outbound
#                                                  ActivityPub
#                                                  delivery across
#                                                  M federation
#                                                  worker processes
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from crates/server/src/lib.rs
#                       clap-derive `CmdArgs` struct + `CmdSubcommand`
#                       enum + `MigrationSubcommand` enum;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of crates/server/src/lib.rs)
#
#   lemmy_server [OPTIONS] [SUBCOMMAND]
#
#   Options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#     --disable-scheduled-tasks      Don't run scheduled tasks
#                                    [env: LEMMY_DISABLE_SCHEDULED_TASKS]
#     --disable-http-server          Disable the HTTP server
#                                    (useful for a Lemmy server
#                                    process that only performs
#                                    scheduled tasks or activity
#                                    sending)
#                                    [env: LEMMY_DISABLE_HTTP_SERVER]
#     --disable-activity-sending     Disable sending outgoing
#                                    ActivityPub messages (only
#                                    pass this for horizontally
#                                    scaled setups; see https://
#                                    join-lemmy.org/docs/
#                                    administration/
#                                    horizontal_scaling.html)
#                                    [env: LEMMY_DISABLE_ACTIVITY_SENDING]
#     --federate-process-index <N>   Index of this outgoing
#                                    federation process (1≤i≤N)
#                                    [default: 1]
#                                    [env: LEMMY_FEDERATE_PROCESS_INDEX]
#     --federate-process-count <N>   How many outgoing federation
#                                    processes you are starting
#                                    in total
#                                    [default: 1]
#                                    [env: LEMMY_FEDERATE_PROCESS_COUNT]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     migration <run|revert> [OPTIONS]
#                                    Do something with diesel
#                                    schema migrations, then exit
#         run                        Run `up.sql` for pending
#                                    migrations, oldest to newest
#         revert                     Run `down.sql` for non-
#                                    pending migrations, newest
#                                    to oldest
#         --all                      Stop after there are no
#                                    remaining migrations
#         --number <N>               Stop after the given number
#                                    of migrations  [default: 1]
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `lemmy_server` declares a **direct** dependency on
#   `activitypub_federation` (workspace dep) in its
#   `crates/server/Cargo.toml`, and the `crates/server/src/lib.rs`
#   entry point imports `activitypub_federation::config::{
#   FederationConfig, FederationMiddleware}` directly
#   (verified via raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of both files).
#
#   `LemmyNet/activitypub-federation-rust` is **THE canonical
#   Rust ActivityPub server framework** — a high-level Rust
#   crate that provides typed:
#
#     • `FederationConfig::<DataType>::builder().domain(...)
#       .app_data(...).build().await` typed federation context
#       builder that wraps actor-key management, HTTP Signature
#       signing, RSA key generation, in-flight queue management,
#       and per-domain rate limiting
#     • `FederationMiddleware` actix-web / axum / poem middleware
#       that auto-injects the typed `Data<FederationConfig>` into
#       every request handler
#     • `Object` trait — implement this on your own typed
#       database-backed types (Lemmy's `ApubPost`, `ApubComment`,
#       `ApubCommunity`, `ApubPerson`, `ApubSite` types all
#       implement `Object<DataType=LemmyContext, Kind=...,
#       Error=LemmyError>` with `from_json` / `into_json` /
#       `verify` / `delete` typed lifecycle methods)
#     • `Activity` trait — implement on your typed Activity
#       types (`CreatePost`, `UpdatePost`, `LikePost`,
#       `FollowCommunity`, etc.) with `verify` + `receive`
#       typed handlers
#     • `Collection` trait — typed federated collection
#       (ordered + unordered) builder for the Outbox / Inbox /
#       Followers / Following / Featured / Likes / Shares
#       collection endpoints
#     • `protocol::verification::verify_domains_match(actor,
#       object)` / `verify_urls_match(a, b)` / `verify_is_remote_object(url,
#       config)` typed verifiers
#     • `protocol::values::MediaTypeMarkdown` /
#       `MediaTypeMarkdownOrHtml` typed AS Note-content
#       media-type discriminator
#     • `protocol::public_key::PublicKey` /
#       `protocol::context::WithContext<Inner>` typed @context
#       wrapper
#     • `fetch::object_id::ObjectId<Kind>` typed AP object URL
#       newtype with built-in `dereference(data)` cached fetcher
#     • `fetch::webfinger::webfinger_resolve_actor(query, config)`
#       typed `acct:user@domain` → `ObjectId<Person>` resolver
#     • `activity_queue::SendActivityTask` / `queue_activity`
#       typed deferred-delivery primitives
#     • `http_signatures::sign_request(req, public_key,
#       private_key)` / `verify_inbox_hash(headers, body)`
#       /  `signing_actor(req, expected_domain, public_key,
#       payload)` typed Sec-Fetch signature primitives
#     • `traits::ActivityHandler` super-trait with the typed
#       `verify` + `receive` lifecycle that every federated
#       activity passes through
#
#   `activitypub-federation-rust` is **the canonical Rust
#   ActivityPub server framework** powering not only Lemmy
#   but also a growing set of Rust ActivityPub-speaking servers:
#   the sublinks/sublinks-rs project (alternative Lemmy-compatible
#   server), the kbin/mbin Rust port project, the
#   piefed/piefed-rust port project, divedb (the federated
#   diving-log platform), rustyverse, scikiwi (the federated
#   genome-database service), oeee-cafe (the federated café-rating
#   platform), and dozens of community projects building
#   ActivityPub-native federated apps in Rust.
#
#   ActivityPub itself is the **W3C Recommendation
#   (REC-activitypub-20180123)** for federated social-web
#   protocols — the underlying decentralized social-graph
#   substrate that joins Mastodon (the canonical microblogging
#   platform, ~700k+ monthly active users across thousands of
#   instances), Lemmy (the link-aggregator), Pleroma + Akkoma
#   (the Elixir-based microblogging server), Misskey + Sharkey
#   + Calckey + Firefish + Iceshrimp (the rich-text microblog
